# PowerShell scripts must be stored as UTF-8 with BOM.
# PowerShell 5.1 (Windows PowerShell) does not detect UTF-8 without BOM and
# falls back to the system ANSI codepage (Windows-1252 on English systems).
# Characters whose UTF-8 byte sequences contain 0x93 or 0x94 — which map to
# curly double-quotes in Windows-1252 — are misread as string terminators,
# causing cascading parse errors.  The BOM (EF BB BF) prevents this entirely.
*.ps1 text working-tree-encoding=UTF-8 eol=crlf

# All other text files: LF in the repo, CRLF on Windows checkout
*     text=auto eol=crlf
*.md  text eol=crlf
*.json text eol=crlf
*.csproj text eol=crlf
*.sln  text eol=crlf
